Representatives of different groups in the Osogbo Local Government Area have hailed the Osun State Governor, Mr Adegboyega Oyetola, on the food support initiative of his administration. A statement on Sunday said the beneficiaries described the governor as a promise keeper. The Secretary-General, Ohaneze Ndigbo group in Osun, Chief Chinaka Bennett, in the statement appreciated Oyetola for his sustained efforts at alleviating the sufferings of the masses. The representative of the Muslim Community in the state, Alhaji Kelani Raji, also lauded the food initiative scheme as a step in the right direction. Similarly, Mr Adedokun Waheed, representing artisans in Osogbo, was quoted as saying “The scheme is an evidence of the governor’s deep concern for the peoples’ welfare.” In the same vein, the representative of Fulani Community and the public relations officer of the Miyetti Allah Group in Osun State, Mohammed Abdullah, said the Osun Food Support Scheme was an historical feat in the state. A representative of the Persons with Disabilities in Osogbo, Adebayo Muritala, said, “This is not the first time Governor Oyetola has factored in citizens, especially People with Disabilities in the programmes of his government.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com